                        ܐܦܝܣܩܘܦܐ ܕܕܝܘܩܐܣܪܝܐ
                </span></span></h1></div><div xmlns:x="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:local="http://syriaca.org/ns"><div class="tei-note"><span xml:lang="en" lang="en" dir="ltr">Bishop of Diocaesarea in Isauria who brought charges against archdeacon
                        Callistus on the ground that he had bought his priestly order and
                        status</span><span class="tei-footnote-refs" dir="ltr" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><span class="tei-footnote-ref"><a href="#bib2458-2">2</a></span> </span></div><div style="margin:0 1em 1em; color: #999999;"><small><p><span class="srp-label"><strong>Syriaca.org URI</strong></span>: <span id="syriaca-id"><a href="http://syriaca.org/person/2458">http://syriaca.org/person/2458</a></span></p></small></div></div><div xmlns:x="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:local="http://syriaca.org/ns" class="row"><div class="col-md-8"><div class="sources"><h3>Personal Information</h3><h4>Name variant(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-listPerson">
                    <span class="tei-person">
                        <span class="tei-persName"> God-loving Bishop Hilarian
                        </span>
                    </span>
                </span> <a href="/3046-9" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Sex: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Hilarian</span> was male. <a href="/3046-10" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Occupation(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Hilarian</span> was a bishop. <a href="/3046-11" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Relationships</h3><p class="indent">Hilarian had
                            enmity for Paul. <a href="/3046-24" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Hilarian and
                                Anonymi
                                3065 shared the Eucharist. <a href="/3046-27" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Hilarian
                            ordained Anonymi
                                3074. <a href="/3055-4" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Musonius and
                                Hilarian
                            brought legal charges or a petition against Eustace. <a href="/3025-41" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Paul brought
                            legal charges or a petition against Hilarian. <a href="/3055-5" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Hilarian and
                                Musonius
                            were part of Anonymi 3723. <a href="/3025-9" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent"> After a dispute with Hilarian about a monastery and a presumptuous and
                            illeagl forging of signatures by Callistus, Paul fled to
                                the royal
                                city.  <a href="/3046-33" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> Until an investigation can be undertaken, Severus believed that
                                Callistus
                            and those who sided from Hilarian should be censored from ministry.  <a href="/3046-34" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> When Paul
                            criticized Hilarian for ordaining priests outside his
                            jurisdiction, Severus had initially prohibited those priests from
                            ministering until an investigation could take place; with Paul's absence,
                                Severus now
                            believed that those men should be reinstated.  <a href="/3055-8" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/></div><div class="citation"><h3>How to cite:</h3><span class="element">
                                “Person Page for <span id="title"><span>Hilarian — ܐܝܠܐܪܝܐܢܘܣ
                        ܐܦܝܣܩܘܦܐ ܕܕܝܘܩܐܣܪܝܐ
                </span></span>,” 
                                in SPEAR: Syriac Persons Events and Relations, general editor Daniel L. Schwartz, 
                                https://dev.spear-prosop.org/aggregate/person/2458.html, 2025-06-24.
                            </span></div></div><div class="col-md-4"><h4>Related taxonomy(s)</h4><ul><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/authority.html"><span class="loadRDF getLabel" data-rdfRef="http://syriaca.org/taxonomy/authority"/>Authority</a></li><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/bishops.html"><span class="loadRDF getLabel" data-rdfRef="http://syriaca.org/taxonomy/bishops"/>Bishops</a></li><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/bringer-of-legal-charges-against.html"><span class="loadRDF getLabel" data-rdfRef="http://syriaca.org/taxonomy/bringer-of-legal-charges-against"/>Bringer of Legal Charges against</a></li><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/clergy.html"><span class="loadRDF getLabel" data-rdfRef="http://syriaca.org/taxonomy/clergy"/>Clergy</a></li><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/commune-together.html"><span class="loadRDF getLabel" data-rdfRef="http://syriaca.org/taxonomy/commune-together"/>Commune Together</a></li><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/enmity-for.html"><span class="loadRDF getLabel" data-rdfRef="http://syriaca.org/taxonomy/enmity-for"/>Enmity for</a></li><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/evil.html"><span class="loadRDF getLabel" data-rdfRef="http://syriaca.org/taxonomy/evil"/>Evil</a></li><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/justice.html"><span class="loadRDF getLabel" data-rdfRef="http://syriaca.org/taxonomy/justice"/>Justice</a></li><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/men.html"><span class="loadRDF getLabel" data-rdfRef="http://syriaca.org/taxonomy/men"/>Men</a></li><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/monasteries.html"><span class="loadRDF getLabel" data-rdfRef="http://syriaca.org/taxonomy/monasteries"/>Monasteries</a></li><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/ordained.html"><span class="loadRDF getLabel" data-rdfRef="http://syriaca.org/taxonomy/ordained"/>Ordained</a></li><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/ordination.html"><span class="loadRDF getLabel" data-rdfRef="http://syriaca.org/taxonomy/ordination"/>Ordination</a></li><li><a href="/aggregate/taxonomy/priests.h